api_list.name: songs/detect
api_list.description:
You may check the tutorial at https://rapidapi.com/apidojo/api/shazam/tutorials.
Detect songs from raw sound data. The raw sound data must be 44100Hz, 1 channel (Mono), signed 16 bit PCM little endian. Other types of media are NOT supported, such as : mp3, wav, etc... or need to be converted to uncompressed raw data. If the result is empty, your request data must be in wrong format in most case. Encoded base64 string of byte[] that generated from raw data less than 500KB (3-5 seconds sample are good enough for detection) will be sent via body as plain text
api_list.code:
import requests

url = "https://shazam.p.rapidapi.com/songs/detect"

headers = {
    "X-RapidAPI-Key": "SIGN-UP-FOR-KEY",
    "X-RapidAPI-Host": "shazam.p.rapidapi.com"
}

response = requests.post(url, headers=headers)

print(response.json())

api_list.name: songs/v2/detect
api_list.description:
You may check the tutorial at https://rapidapi.com/apidojo/api/shazam/tutorials.
Detect songs from raw sound data. The raw sound data must be 44100Hz, 1 channel (Mono), signed 16 bit PCM little endian. Other types of media are NOT supported, such as : mp3, wav, etc... or need to be converted to uncompressed raw data. If the result is empty, your request data must be in wrong format in most case. Encoded base64 string of byte[] that generated from raw data less than 500KB (3-5 seconds sample are good enough for detection) will be sent via body as plain text

optional_parameters.name: timestamp
optional_parameters.description: This parameter is used to indicate that you are detecting the same song while making different calls in case the previous portion of sound cannot be recognized successfully. You simply use the same unix timestamp (milliseconds) which is the starting time of first sound portion of detecting progress. This parameter must be come along with \"samplems\" parameter. Ex : 1591884466431

optional_parameters.name: samplems
optional_parameters.description: The samplems in milliseconds including the total duration of previous sound portions if any. Otherwise just provide the samplems of the current sound portion. Ex : First portion is 5040, second portion is 9040, etc...

optional_parameters.name: identifier
optional_parameters.description:
This parameter is used to indicate that you are detecting the same song while making different calls in case the previous portion of sound cannot be recognized successfully. You simply use the same id string while detecting the same song. This parameter must be come along with \"samplems\" parameter.
The format is xxxxxxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx, Ex : 21abe4d2-0fe9-4be4-8492-0ecf26960f7e.

Detect songs from raw sound data. The raw sound data must be 44100Hz, 1 channel (Mono), signed 16 bit PCM little endian. Other types of media are NOT supported, such as : mp3, wav, etc... or need to be converted to uncompressed raw data. If the result is empty, your request data must be in wrong format in most case. Encoded base64 string of byte[] that generated from raw data less than 500KB (3-5 seconds sample are good enough for detection) will be sent via body as plain text

optional_parameters.name: timestamp
optional_parameters.description: This parameter is used to indicate that you are detecting the same song while making different calls in case the previous portion of sound cannot be recognized successfully. You simply use the same unix timestamp (milliseconds) which is the starting time of first sound portion of detecting progress. This parameter must be come along with \"samplems\" parameter. Ex : 1591884466431

optional_parameters.name: samplems
optional_parameters.description: The samplems in milliseconds including the total duration of previous sound portions if any. Otherwise just provide the samplems of the current sound portion. Ex : First portion is 5040, second portion is 9040, etc...

optional_parameters.name: identifier
optional_parameters.description:
This parameter is used to indicate that you are detecting the same song while making different calls in case the previous portion of sound cannot be recognized successfully. You simply use the same id string while detecting the same song. This parameter must be come along with \"samplems\" parameter.
The format is xxxxxxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx, Ex : 21abe4d2-0fe9-4be4-8492-0ecf26960f7e.
